H0.text: Name the earliest (post-gamete) developmental stage of the human embryo. Morula

H1.text: Name the earliest (post-gamete) developmental stage of the human embryo. Blastocyst

H2.text: Name the earliest (post-gamete) developmental stage of the human embryo. Embryoblast

H3.text: Name the earliest (post-gamete) developmental stage of the human embryo. Zygote

A4.text: The zygote is the earliest developmental stage.

A5.text: Through the processes of compaction, cell division, and blastulation, the conceptus takes the form of the blastocyst by the fifth day of development, just as it approaches the site of implantation.
